onse": "```python\nfrom typing import List\n\nclass Solution:\n    def minPairSum(self, nums: List[int]) -> int:\n        # Sort the array to pair the smallest and largest elements\n        nums.sort()\n        # Initialize the maximum pair sum to a very small number\n        max_pair_sum = 0\n        # Pair the smallest element with the largest, second smallest with second largest, etc.\n        for i in range(len(nums) // 2):\n            pair_sum = nums[i] + nums[-(i + 1)]\n            # Update the maximum pair sum if the current pair sum is larger\n            max_pair_sum = max(max_pair_sum, pair_sum)\n        return max_pair_sum\n```\n\nThis solution sorts the input list `nums` and pairs the smallest element with the largest, the second smallest with the second largest, and so on. By doing this, it minimizes the maximum pair sum. The function then returns this minimized maximum pair sum.", "estimated_date": 1621728000000}